      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): share approval runtime socket token",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Use the existing `exec-approvals.json` socket token as the approval-runtime token when it exists, so Docker/CLI/separate-process approval clients sharing `OPENCLAW_HOME` can authenticate as the local approval runtime.\n- Keep the process-local random token as the fallback when no shared socket token exists, without creating `exec-approvals.json` just to read a token.\n- Keep `approvalRuntimeToken` attached only for generated local gateway URL sources; env, explicit, and configured remote URL sources omit it even when the host is loopback.\n\n## Scope split\n- Split out from #86771.\n- This PR is only shared approval-runtime token selection for Docker/CLI/separate-process approval clients sharing OpenClaw state.\n- It does not include stale Discord button UX or the `approval.routeNotice.send` gateway method.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: A separate approval-runtime process sharing `OPENCLAW_HOME` can authenticate with the existing `exec-approvals.json` socket token and resolve a requester-bound approval. Env/configured remote gateway URL sources still omit `approvalRuntimeToken` and cannot resolve requester-bound approvals without normal owner visibility/runtime authority.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on PR head `a395cede70`, Node `v24.14.0`, macOS host. The smoke used an isolated temporary `OPENCLAW_HOME`, a real `exec-approvals.json` socket token, a real loopback gateway server, a parent Node process, a separate child Node process, and real gateway clients.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a `pnpm exec tsx` smoke from the repo root. The smoke wrote a temporary `.openclaw/exec-approvals.json`, started a real gateway, created requester-bound approvals, ran a child Node process sharing `OPENCLAW_HOME` to resolve one approval through `withOperatorApprovalsGatewayClient`, then checked that env override and configured remote loopback clients could connect but could not resolve requester-bound approvals.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ PATH=\"$HOME/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH\" pnpm exec tsx <shared-runtime-current-head-smoke>\n[gateway] starting HTTP server...\n[gateway] http server listening (0 plugins)\n[gateway] ready\nSMOKE shared_runtime_current_head ok {\"head\":\"a395cede70\",\"gatewayUrl\":\"ws://127.0.0.1:<port>\",\"sharedTokenFile\":\"<OPENCLAW_HOME>/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json\",\"childProcess\":\"CHILD_SHARED_RUNTIME_RESOLVE ok\",\"envOverrideRejected\":true,\"remoteLoopbackRejected\":true,\"sharedResolve\":\"allow-once\"}\n[shutdown] completed cleanly in 14ms\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The second process resolved the requester-bound approval using the shared socket token. Env override and configured remote loopback clients could connect to the gateway, but both were rejected from resolving requester-bound approvals because those URL sources do not receive `approvalRuntimeToken`.\n\nWhat was not tested: No Docker Compose smoke was run. The live proof used two Node processes on one host sharing `OPENCLAW_HOME`. Explicit `gatewayUrl` override omission is covered by focused client-option tests because this helper path has no explicit auth input and cannot authenticate to a token-auth gateway as a live remote client.\n\n## Tests and validation\n- `PATH=\"$HOME/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH\" pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/gateway/operator-approval-runtime-token.ts src/gateway/operator-approval-runtime-token.test.ts src/gateway/operator-approvals-client.ts src/gateway/operator-approvals-client.test.ts src/gateway/operator-approvals-client.e2e.test.ts` — passed.\n- `PATH=\"$HOME/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH\" node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/operator-approval-runtime-token.test.ts src/gateway/operator-approvals-client.test.ts src/gateway/operator-approvals-client.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot` — 5 files, 29 tests passed.\n- `git diff --check upstream/main..HEAD` — passed.\n\n## Risk checklist\nDid user-visible behavior change? `Yes`\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? `No`\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? `Yes`\n\nHighest-risk area: approval-runtime authentication for local approval clients sharing OpenClaw state.\n\nMitigation: Shared-token selection only reads an existing socket token; it does not create the shared file. The approval client attaches the runtime token only for generated local gateway URL sources; env, explicit, and configured remote URL sources omit it.\n",
        "branch": "codex/shared-approval-runtime-token",
